{"name":"Charge","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character knows how to deliver a well-aimed blow at the end of a charge.</p>\n<p>If the hero performs a run action and ends his movement for the round adjacent to an opponent, he may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action} penalty). This cannot be combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0Po3UEBs0JLPCFiT"}
{"name":"Spell Finesse","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero is particularly adept with one power.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be chosen once per rank. Each time he picks this Edge he may pick one of the options below and apply it to one power he knows. Each option may only be picked once per individual power, but the same option can be applied to different spells and different options can be given to the same spell. For instance, a mage can take an increased Wild Die and AP 2 for his <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}&nbsp;</em>spell, but he cannot take AP 2 twice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Arcane:</strong> The hero increases his arcane skill Wild Die by one die type when casting the spell.</li>\n<li><strong>Armor Penetration: </strong>A damaging spell has AP 2. This counts against Armor provided by Arcane Resistance and stacks with any other similar bonus, such as an acid trapping.</li>\n<li><strong>Heavy Weapon: </strong>A damaging spell counts as a Heavy Weapon. It does not gain any AP value.</li>\n<li><strong>Range: </strong>The hero treats his relevant attribute as one step higher for the purpose of determining the spell&rsquo;s Range. Fixed range spells (such as bolt) have their range increased by 2/4/8. Touch and Self spells are unaffected by this ability.</li>\n<li><strong>Selective: </strong>When casting a spell with a template effect, the caster decides who is and isn&rsquo;t affected, to a maximum of half his arcane skill die. For instance, a mage with an arcane skill of d8 can drop a <em>blast </em>over a group of allies and foes and cause no damage to four of his comrades.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any), Arcana d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0nC21U2FSt1owpZG"}
