{"name":"Siege Mentality","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character has a strong defensive mentality and understands how to make the most of his fortification and its defenders.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, he increases the Siege Bonus of any fortification he defends by +1.</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase this bonus by an additional +1 for success and +2 with a raise by studying and better defending weak areas.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CnjVC7G1ro8uYWNt"}
{"name":"Improved Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</p>\n<p>If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to recover.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Focus"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CpUKSBFZPlkOmmFA"}
{"name":"Improved Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 2 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. If the dwarf gets a raise on the attack roll, he ignores 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sunder"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"D0Q9v8C7ucMKzjwJ"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Psionics)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Arcane Background (Psionics)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Psionics d4+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DFn4vB7waDPRgUcE"}
{"name":"Overload Metabolism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged can heal damage at a cost to his other physical attributes by exciting his warforged metabolism. Once per session, he can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair damage. On a success, he repairs one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}. On a raise, he repairs two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wounds}. Doing this reduces his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} by one die type for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>If the warforged is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Incapacitated} and has not yet used this ability, any use of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]{Imbue Item} Edge targeted upon him automatically activates this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Agility d8+, Strength d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"G1lV08ImYh1hkOnW"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Flame","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GHKUr9Ms4KhZOc9H"}
{"name":"Strong Caster","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage is adept at channeling raw magical essence.</p>\n<p>A mage with this Edge reduces the initial Casting Modifier of all spells by 1, to a minimum of zero. For instance, a spell with a Casting Modifier of &minus;2 only inflicts a &minus;1 penalty to this mage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background, arcane skill d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Gb1QkGhFX6qYaYsp"}
{"name":"Attune Arcane Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some artificers become adept at eking every advantage out of an arcane device's enchanted qualities.</p>\n<p>When wielding a weapon that is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane device}, artificers with this Edge gain a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls. They must spend 24 hours with a newly acquired magic weapon before they can gain this benefit when wielding it.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Gvj4W8Hx0unUzXJb"}
{"name":"Drop!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a ranged weapon targets an ally within the hero's command radius, the character may order him to drop to the ground. This allows the intended target to fall @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn, even if he has acted already, gaining the benefits of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Medium Cover}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Gw2SPJw6CbHgtqzA"}
{"name":"Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Enchant allows a character to craft \"enchanted items.\" These are devices which essentially allow the user&mdash;whether he's a spellcaster or not&mdash;to cast whatever power the item is imbued with.</p>\n<p>They require an item that was crafted with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} stored into the item requires are least 25 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards times the positive of the Casting Modifier of the power put into the item. Each die type for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Skill} roll requires and additional 50 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards up to the a maximum die type of what the caster has at the time of its creation. The crafter has to have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Powers]{Power} available to be able to enchant an item.</p>\n<p>The casting and crafting time is equal to 1 day per 25 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards. At the end the artificer may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll at &ndash;4. If he fails on the roll, then all the materials have been used but then&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>An artificer with a d10 in Magecraft can enchant a permanent <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Blast]{blast}</em> (&ndash;2 Casting Modifier) wand with a d8 Arcane skill for 200 galfiars and 10 power points an additional 500 galifars. Work on this wand would take 24 days to create.</p>\n<p>Items created through this Edge are referred to as minor artifacts. Items recharge at the standard rate of one power Point per hour. The wielder cannot use his own @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;with enchanted items&mdash;they are effectively \"locked.\"</p>\n<p>While a character can add further powers to his own devices, he cannot alter those of others.</p>\n<p>The user can decide which powers he's activating when he makes his arcane skill roll, however. He may also make a single roll for all the powers the device has. If a hero carries a ring enchanted with invisibility and armor, for example, both powers must share its pool of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, but the wearer can decide whether to activate only one of its powers or both with a single roll.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magic, Magecraft, or Miracles), Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HBdN4xFFnIlHdLHN"}
{"name":"Filthy Rich","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>This fortunate individual is very wealthy. He has five times the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds}&nbsp;for the setting during character creation. If a regular income is appropriate for this setting, the hero receives a 8d4 x 300 galifars annual salary, or 6d4 x 30 galifars monthly stipend.</p>\n<p>Even wealthier characters may exist, but unless there&rsquo;s a game effect it probably shouldn&rsquo;t matter. This should be worked out with the GM and come with many more assets as well as onerous responsibilities</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rich"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JJbLwSBvAq0XcH4X"}
{"name":"Improved Giant Killer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero may choose to ignore the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} of a creature three sizes or more than them. This Edge does not work with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area effect attacks}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Giant Killer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JjxYOmIexXFy9N3d"}
{"name":"Rich","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he&rsquo;s got more money than most. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Rich heroes start with three times the normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds} for the setting. If a regular income is appropriate for this setting, the hero receives a 7d4 x 100 galifars annual salary, or 5d4 x 10 galifars monthly stipend.​</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Juet9Oa5swYcApI0"}
