{"name":"University Trained","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You attended one of the prestigious universities in the world. You like to read, and you absorb the information like a sponge. These books can be found in classrooms, in libraries or even in the local coffee shop. Book Learning confers 4 additional skill points on the Character, but these points must be spent on the following: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Cosmology]{Cosmology}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Religion]{Religion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} </em>or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Science]{Science}.</p>\n<p>Because of your interest in books, a character with this Edge gains one additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language} at a d4.</p>\n<p><strong>Special: </strong>This Edge must be taken during character creation or after actually going to one of the schools of Khorvaire with DM approval.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OaGYjYT6C9pkISnc"}
{"name":"Aristocrat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}&nbsp;Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the GM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his GM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the GM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. GMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OiZ9VvGDMGEBOVsh"}
{"name":"Scamper","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Halflings are small and quick. Some make great use of this in combat too, scampering about to avoid the blows of larger foes. Opponents of man-size or larger subtract 1 from attack rolls against halflings with this Edge. The benefit only applies when the character is aware the attack is coming, he is unbound and able to move freely, and has no encumbrance penalty.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Halfling, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OkrPqGvo9hCPABHf"}
{"name":"Explorer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>There are two extremes of climate in the world, and this character has survived them both. He gains a +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} rolls. in addition, he adds +2 to resist the effects of heat and cold related enviromental hazards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+, Survival d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PzOqvWIKHwdwy28D"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Dragonmarked Focus d4+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QPSbpQAO2sZKW4DR"}
{"name":"Help Me!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Once per round when a foe moves adjacent to the hero, the threatened character may call for help. One ally within the character&rsquo;s command radius who has not yet acted this turn may try to interrupt as if he were on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold}. With a success, the ally must attack the opponent who triggered this Edge.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QgdZyLRrTuj3IM3S"}
{"name":"Arcane Device","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer is able to arcane devices imbued with mystical arcane power including items such as potions, scrolls, brooches, and other single use temporary objects. Creating more permanent items is takes much more skill and training.</p>\n<p>To create a arcane device, the artificer must know the power he wishes to imbue, have access to a workspace, and basic tools (a tool kit relavant to the device being created). Creating the device requires two hours and eberron dragonshards costing 25 galifars per Casting Modifier of the power being imbued. To make a potion of <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Farsight]{farsight}</em> (&minus;2), for example, requires four hours of preparation and 50 galifars of eberron dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When imbuing powers with variable effects, the exact use must be chosen when the item is created. For example, an artificer creating a potion with <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost/lower Trait} </em>must choose which @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} is affected at the time of creation. Powers requiring an opposed or attack roll can&rsquo;t be imbued into an arcane device, so <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{lower Trait} </em>&nbsp;is not an option and the item boosts by default.</p>\n<p>At the end of the preparation time the artificer makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll but Casting Modifiers do not apply. With a success the item is created and may be used by anyone, gaining the benefits of the power imbued. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Raises} work as normal increasing the effect of the imbued power. With a failed casting the raw materials are consumed, while a critical failure means the artificer suffers the effects of Backlash for his Arcane Background.</p>\n<p>Powers with a Range other than Touch or Self must be thrown. These devices require an attack roll using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} skill and have a Range of 3/6/12. Other items require an action to activate dependent on the specific item (drinking a potion, reading a scroll, applying a salve, rubbing a brooch, etc.) and the item is consumed or loses its power.</p>\n<p>Except for Instant powers, the Duration of the power is 2d6 hours.</p>\n<p>An artificer may only have a number of arcane devices created at one time equal to half his @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana]{Arcana} skill die.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Dragonmark of Making, Magecraft, Magic, or Miracles), Arcana d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Qt6njzY3H3KIoOXs"}
{"name":"Knight","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Knights are chivalric heroes dedicated to a particular cause. All Knights swear holy oaths to their patron, whether it is a god, an order, or a noble, and must answer the call when summoned&mdash;even if it means his certain death.</p>\n<p>Upon acceptance into his order, a knight is gifted with the tools of his trade&mdash;a light warhorse, a lance, chain mail armor, and a medium shield emblazoned with the symbol of his patron.</p>\n<p>In addition to these material rewards, Knights of good causes gain +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+, Fighting d8+, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"R498Zqsx5XLvC5ws"}
{"name":"Bodyguard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to intercept blows meant for others. At the start of his turn the character may nominate one adjacent ally. So long as the ally remains adjacent, the ally uses the hero&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} in place of his own. This benefit is immediately lost if the parrying character is rendered incapable of parrying a blow.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Agility d8, Block, Notice d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Re3jFHhrZgowQamQ"}
{"name":"Improved Primal Fury","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With sufficient willpower, a hero who has learned to trigger his rage can restrain it as well. Improved Primal Fury allows the hero to ignore the &ndash;2 penalty to end his rage, and on a Critical Failure, he will not hit an ally while @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} (though he may still hit the wrong opponent or miss).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Primal Fury, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Rvu5t0gCjIyiM7IX"}
{"name":"Disciple of Olladra","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SOb3vnKqx7ZBTl3o"}
{"name":"Mighty Shot","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has learned how to use his full strength with a bow. The character calculates damage with his bow as Str+d6, instead of a flat 2d6.</p>\n<p>Mighty shot does not work with crossbows or other ranged weapons&mdash;only with bows and long bows.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d8+, Shooting d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TRUB1KwBLVVMJFQa"}
