{"name":"Focus","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wielding arcane power has its drawbacks, but some people learn to keep their focus even when things don't go right.</span></p>\n<p>If a character with this Edge is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Shaken} as a result of failing to invoke a spell, he gets an immediate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at &ndash;2 to recover.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), Spirit d6+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dEnAg8KoBCpspEo3"}
{"name":"Improved Bilge Rat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Scuttling around in the bowels of the ship doesn&rsquo;t suit every sailor, but this character has learned to adjust to the cramped conditions below deck.</p>\n<p>The character can use any weapon below decks without incurring the &ndash;2 penalty for fighting in cramped conditions.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bilge Rat"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dLqNhgkaPCEepJw9"}
{"name":"Master Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Truly experienced artificers can inscribe runes of power that provide an item with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Edges]{Edge}. This work uses the same basic rules of \"fiddling\" as from the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]{Artificer} edge, with two notable differences.</p>\n<p>Firstly, while the character need not have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Edges]{Edge} he is placing into an item, he must be of the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{rank}. For instance, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran} character could not inscribe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved First Strike]{Improved First Strike}. Secondly with this more powerful magic, at least 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards are required for the imbueing.</p>\n<p>An individual item may contain no more than three Edges (again, items with more are considered true relics and beyond the ken of characters). Where an Edge requires another Edge as a requirement (such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy} needing @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy}), the requirement Edge must be worked into the item first and uses one of the item's three Edge \"slots.\"</p>\n<p>Edges placed in items allow anyone wearing or carrying the object (as appropriate) to gain the benefits of the Edge without needing to meet the requirements.</p>\n<p>An item must be worn or a weapon drawn to gain the effects of the Edge. Simply owning an axe of the berserker does not grant one the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking: </strong>Some Edges, typically those granting a fixed bonus, do stack with Edges possessed by the wielder.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Adept Artificer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dytLYCXAE0GD0PGQ"}
