{"name":"Running Throw","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to use his momentum to boost the range of thrown weapons.</p>\n<p>If the character moves at least half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} immediately before making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to throw a weapon he increases the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} of his thrown weapon by 2/4/8. No other actions may be performed between moving and throwing, and the two maneuvers must be taken in the same round.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Strength d8, Athletics d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fpjJZSPX598K1V1Q"}
{"name":"Brutal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character with this @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{edge} is more dangerous when roughed up. When determining melee damage, he adds his wound level to the roll. A hero with 3 wounds, for instance, adds +3 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Wild Card"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fqqM6p9Xq4y8uikA"}
{"name":"Siege Breaker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The hero has a good knowledge of siege warfare and can spot weaknesses in enemy fortifications.</p>\n<p>When he leads the army, the character reduces the Siege Bonus of any fortification his men are attacking by 1 (to a minimum of zero).</p>\n<p>If he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll at the start of a siege, he can increase the Siege Bonus penalty by an additional &ndash;1 for success and &ndash;2 with a raise by studying and exploiting specific weaknesses.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fyKyhVnXMbgpXX3o"}
{"name":"Natural Swimmer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Your hero wasn't literally born in the water, but some might believe he was. He takes to it like a fish and can hold his breath longer than most others. Natural swimmers add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll for Swimmings, add +1 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} swimming, and can hold their breath 50% longer than others of their species.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"glmfSdOyzG7sjnN8"}
{"name":"Legendary Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The party gains +1d8 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory} for each raise after the first when using the Variable Glory Awards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Master Storyteller"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hJLphEULKMS7cli0"}
{"name":"Steal Away","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero uses distraction and cover to slip away from his foes.</p>\n<p>The character may make a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid attack when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing from Melee]{Withdrawing} from close combat. He suffers a -1 penalty for each adjacent foe. Failure means foes may attack as normal as the adventurer withdraws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hWvygsld2znCTaAB"}
{"name":"Shifter Stamina","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some shifters can persist with endurance beyond most others. Shifters with this Edge are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal damage}, and the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} are suppressed. When their shifting ends, any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} effects that would have taken effect during shifting (or that were in effect when shifting began) take effect normally.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (Any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"i9p4d7OSz3kkU5st"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Six","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iB1pZhTEFhfscgdq"}
{"name":"Bilge Rat","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Scuttling around in the bowels of the ship doesn&rsquo;t suit every sailor, but this character has learned to adjust to the cramped conditions below deck.</p>\n<p>The character no longer suffers the &ndash;2 penalty when fighting below decks or in small quarters. If the weapon has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}&nbsp;value the &ndash;2 penalty applies as normal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iISIKXjNPnV10ItB"}
{"name":"A Few Good Men","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The character knows how to get the best from the troops at his disposal.</p>\n<p>Once the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{tokens} for each force have been calculated, the character adds one token to his army's total to account for their status.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Inspire, Smarts d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ikODOfdq9LemPKl0"}
{"name":"Coordinated Firepower","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero knows how to coordinate missile fire against a single foe.</p>\n<p>Instead of firing separately, all missile troops within the hero's command radius yet to act in the round can fire as a single unit on the hero's action (this counts as their entire action for the round).</p>\n<p>The hero nominates one foe within range of his weapon. He then makes a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, as appropriate for his weapon. Each additional missile soldier within the hero's command range (and within range of the target), firing at the same time adds a flat +2 to the attack roll.</p>\n<p>Damage is calculated as normal for the hero's weapon, but he adds +1d6 per raise (not just for the first raise). Coordinating fire in this manner counts as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{single action}.</p>\n<p>A hero cannot use Double Shot or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer} in conjunction with this Edge unless all subordinates firing with the hero have those Edges as well.</p>\n<p>Although the soldiers lose their individual attacks, the combined firepower gives a better chance of bringing down a large foe (like a dragon), and unlike separate missile fire, the entire damage roll is applied once against the foe's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Command, Smarts d6+, Athletics or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ikchrlPpqe91Oi2J"}
{"name":"True Hero","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When lesser men fall by the wayside, this hero just keeps soldiering on.</p>\n<p>When the character takes enough wounds to make him Incapacitated, he may make a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll. Should the roll fail, the hero may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} roll as normal. If a character suffers multiple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} in the same round that take him to Incapacitated, he may make multiple free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Fafhrd already has 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds}, when two vicious wolves sink their teeth into him, inflicting 2 and 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{wounds} respectively. Fafhrd may make two free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls, one against each attack.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Heroic, Iron Jaw"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"j06iQOIOAKs2aPES"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Ancestors","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jQgcy151Rd0la2Ck"}
{"name":"Wrestler","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero is trained in holds, locks, and takedowns. She may roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. She may also roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Crushing}. If she already has a damage die from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Claws}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edges, etc., increase the damage die by one type instead.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jmHtpULOm3p28njF"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Divine Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Divine Magic)]{Arcane Background (Divine Magic)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Faith d4+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"k9JNercUuI84UwmQ"}
{"name":"Fighting Withdrawl","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero can defend himself even while running away. The character may run while using the Defend maneuver.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Agility, Fighting d8"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kIsE4alkxvDZiP2d"}
{"name":"Mounted Combatant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character has a knack for getting the best out of his mount.</p>\n<p>They ignore two points of penalties to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll, and may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for any mount they are riding or command, using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} skill instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}. Each success and raise negates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, he may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} to spur his mount to greater speeds. With success, the mount gains +2 Pace for this round. a failure causes the mount to gain no increase to its Pace and it suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} due to the exertion.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Riding d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lJhR7SY59T3aCK71"}
{"name":"Psicrystal","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A psicrystal is a fragment of a kalashtar's personality, brought into physical form and a semblance of life. It appears as a crystalline construct about the size of a human hand.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Personalities: </strong>A psicrystal has its own personality (a fragment of the owner's personality), which gives its owner a bonus on certain types of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as given on the table below. These special abilities and bonuses apply only when the owner and the psicrystal are within 1 mile of each other.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Bully:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} checks</li>\n<li><em>Friendly: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks</li>\n<li><em>Hero:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Nimble:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} rolls to interrupt actions</li>\n<li><em>Observant: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} checks</li>\n<li><em>Resolved:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls</li>\n<li><em>Sage:</em> +1 bonus on @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} checks</li>\n<li><em>Single-minded: </em>+1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls while maintaining powers</li>\n<li><em>Sneaky: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} checks</li>\n<li><em>Sympathetic: </em>+1 bonus on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smart} rolls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each psicrystal has a distinct personality, chosen by its owner at the time of its creation from among those given on the table. Upon taking this Edge, its owner typically gets a feel for a psicrystal's personality only through occasional impulses, but as the owner increases gains experience, the psicrystal's personality becomes more pronounced.</p>\n<p>As the owner advances, it is not uncommon for a psicrystal to constantly ply its owner with observations and advice, often severely slanted toward the psicrystal's particular worldview. The owner always sees a bit of himself in his psicrystal, even if magnified and therefore distorted.</p>\n<p><strong>Psicrystal Advancement:</strong> At each Rank of the owner, the psicrystal has the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Novice:</em> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] +1; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d4</li>\n<li><em>Seasoned: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+2; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d6</li>\n<li><em>Veteran: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+3; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d8</li>\n<li><em>Heroic: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+4; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d10</li>\n<li><em>Legendary: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]</em>&nbsp;+5; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} d12</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A psicrystal can speak one language of its owner's choice (so long as it is a language the owner knows). A psicrystal can understand all other languages known by its owner, but cannot speak them.</p>\n<p>Because of the telepathic link between a psicrystal and its owner, the owner has the same connection to an item or place that the psicrystal does. For instance, if his psicrystal has seen a room, the owner can teleport into that room as if he has seen it too, negating the -4 penalty for the destination being an unknown area; the -2 penalty for not being able to see it presently might still apply.</p>\n<p>The psicrystal is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} with respect to Wounds and the Wild Die, but has no Prophecy Shards. The owner may spend his for the psicrystal, however.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the psion can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The psion may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the psion to take it again while he's a Novice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The psicrystal gains @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} against psionics.</li>\n<li>The psion can transfer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} levels to or from his psicrystal as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free actions}.</li>\n<li>The psion can use the psicrystal's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the psion's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>Whenever the psicrystal is adjacent to or in the possession of its owner, the owner has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Alertness]{Alertness} Edge.</li>\n<li>Any powers the psion manifests on himself also affect the psicrystal. If he manifests armor with a raise, both he and his psicrystal gain +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor] for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The psicrystal has 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, which the psion may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the psion's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n<li>The psicrystal can act as a conduit for the psion's powers by delivering touch powers manifested by its owner. The owner and the psicrystal must be in contact at the time the power is manifested. The power must be delivered before the owner can manifest another power. At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Legendary} Rank, the owner can manifest the power through the psicrystal to a distance of up to 1 mile.</li>\n<li>At @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Seasoned} Rank or above, the owner, as a standard action, can will his psicrystal to fly with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6. The effect lasts for one day (or until the owner dismisses it, at which point the psicrystal drifts gently to the ground).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If the psicrystal is destroyed, the character must take this Edge again to create a new psicrystal. However, the previous acquisitions of this Edge to add to its abilities are applied to the new psicrystal.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Kalashtar, Arcane Background (Psionics), Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"m6AcXlZtsk8n2zsP"}
{"name":"Extra Shifter Ability","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer come from a mixed lineage of shifters and has one additional shifter ability. They can manifest this additional ability while shifted as well.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shifter (any)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mESAlxwfx1IFI9bJ"}
{"name":"Shieldwall","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge allows a hero to defend a comrade so long as the hero is using a medium or large shield.</p>\n<p>Attacks against one character adjacent to the hero suffer modifiers based on the hero's shield type. If there are multiple heroes with this Edge adjacent to a character or the target has his own shield, only the best modifier applies. A hero adjacent to multiple allies must declare which one he is protecting at the start of his turn.</p>\n<p>The hero also keeps his shield modifier if he is attacked.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Hobgoblin, Block"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mQmA8e3AKNfJbbOW"}
