{"name":"Tinkerer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>On taking this Edge, the artificer may craft (or modify) an item that adds +1 to the user's relevant trait roll, increases the damage of a weapon by +1, or increases the bonus of armor by +1. No activation roll is required.</p>\n<p>Assuming the artificer is always \"fiddling\" with devices (not locked in prison, for example), and has adequate tools, he may make an Artificer roll at &ndash;4 at the end of any session in which he advances. If successful, he adds another +1 to any item of his choice.</p>\n<p>This could be his own wand (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}), the clothing of another (bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}), or any other item of his choice. The item now adds that bonus to the user's relevant trait or damage roll, or armor rating. No item may have more than a +3 bonus.</p>\n<p><strong>Stacking:</strong> Bonuses from items don't stack, so a bow of accuracy +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) wielded by someone with targeting glasses +3 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) gets only the highest of the two.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Crafting d8+, Magecraft d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nAWjXwmPLjhPaMKG"}
{"name":"Improved Enchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Improved Enchant works the same way as @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Enchant]{Enchant} with one important exception--the power is \"always on\" and no longer requires @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} to use (it has infinite points). The cost, however, is 1000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} required to activate the power.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>Enchanting a sword with Smite would require 2000 galifars of Eberron Dragonshards.</p>\n<p>When the device is created, the creator makes an arcane skill roll. Failure means the Eberron Dragonshards are lost (and at the GM's fiat, the device is destroyed as well--or it could become cursed). A success means the power is activated as usual. A raise means the power forever activates with a raise (if desired by the user).</p>\n<p>Artifacts which are always on (a ring of invisibility, a cloak of stealth, and so on), don't require an arcane skill roll to activate&mdash;but may require an action to \"ready\"&mdash;the ring must be put on, the cloak pulled over the shoulder, etc. Thus a ring of invisibility could always be worn and require no activation roll&mdash;but the wearer would always be invisible.</p>\n<p>Artifacts requiring activation, such as a wand of fireballs, require a suitable skill roll (Shooting for wands, for example). All artifacts created using this Edge are called major artifacts.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Gear Toolkit</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Enchant"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_4tm7000wlw","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Legendary Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nB8bT8txNODJidKI"}
{"name":"Master Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Zombies raised by the Necromancer now have an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice (usually @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Necromancer"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nLLpDUZ8XL2lmx6D"}
