{"name":"Oversized Weapon Master","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The character may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{two-handed} melee weapons with one hand. He may only use one such weapon at a time, even if he has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Two-Fisted]{Two-Fisted} Edges, though he may use an oversize weapon in this manner and wield a standard one-handed weapon simultaneously.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Strength d10+, Fighting d10+, Size 0 or greater"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nr6MEHaZ9VvkNf6c"}
{"name":"Master Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Tales of brave heroes and epic battles are told across Khorvaire in taverns and around hearths and campfires. Most master storytellers are skalds or bards.</p>\n<p>When using the Variable @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory}&nbsp;Awards rules (p. 100), the characters roll d8s instead of a d6s if this hero recounts their deeds.</p>\n<p>In addition, the storyteller is adept at deflecting bad press through carefully chosen words. The party suffers no penalties to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory}&nbsp;if the storyteller rolls a critical failure, treating it as a regular failure.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source; Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Persuasion d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"p7GEWHSsjdSEUGOk"}
{"name":"Disciple of Dol Dorn","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":null,"notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Miracles), Agility or Strength d8+, Faith d8+, Fighting d8+, follower of Dol Dorn"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pET3PPg0BuhgUQUF"}
{"name":"Cry Havoc!","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is used only for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}. The general has an uncanny knack for knowing when to unleash his troops and when to hold back.</p>\n<p>Once per battle, during the Battle Roll Phase, the character may declare a charge. He must do this before he or his opponent rolls their Battle die. If the character succeeds in his roll and beats his opponent, his enemy loses one extra token.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Fervor, Spirit d8+, Battle d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"q7pTbJAcaT8Y18SJ"}
{"name":"Holy Adept","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Adepts are holy warriors who have trained themselves to be living weapons. Some do so to be ultimate warriors; others do it in the service of a cause or deity.</p>\n<p>Their unarmed attacks do @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 damage, and they are always considered armed for purposes of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Defender} rule.</p>\n<p>In addition, upon taking this Edge and at each new Rank, they may choose to change the trappings of one of the following powers to work only on themselves but be activated as a free action: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Smite]{Smite}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Speed}. The Adept must have the power to begin with, and this does not allow him to activate more than one power in a round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Miracles), Faith d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qgX5sQNHiX9xdDwq"}
