{"name":"Fanaticism","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is most appropriate for members of the military, but the leader of a seasoned band of monster hunters might develop it as well.</p>\n<p>Troops under command of a character with this Edge add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fervor"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sspLyfU9nihCHWKt"}
{"name":"Rope Monkey","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rope Monkeys are those sailors who may as well have been born in the rigging. They always seem to know just the right rope to cut and pull to swing to some other part of the ship and can ride the lines down to avoid an otherwise nasty fall.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkey has two functions. The first is to allow a character on the exterior of the ship to move to any other exposed part of the ship by swinging from the rigging. This counts as the character&rsquo;s movement and requires a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll. If successful, he moves to any other external area of the ship. He may not move further this action even by \"running.\" With a raise, he can move and gains momentary surprise on any foes, adding +2 to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks and damage rolls for the round. This can also be combined with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} maneuver.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also use this ability in forests with tall trees. In that case, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll is made at &ndash;2 and the character may reposition himself within d10\".</p>\n<p>A foe who wants to take his free attack at a Rope Monkey swinging out of melee must subtract 2 from his roll. The same applies to characters with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}&mdash;they suffer a &ndash;2 penalty to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll.</p>\n<p>Rope Monkeys may also make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll any time they fall from a ship&rsquo;s rigging (and are conscious). Success means they take half the usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling} damage by grabbing onto ropes as they tumble. With a raise, the sailor manages to slide down a rope and suffers no damage.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+, Athletics d10+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tIkqq3INM0LCXS0w"}
{"name":"Guardian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This character might be a professional bodyguard or just intensely devoted, but in either case he can jump in front of attacks intended for another. A character with this Edge must declare whom he is guarding at the beginning of any combat. As long as the guardian stays within 1\" of the chosen person, any attack aimed at that person is automatically rolled against the guardian instead. A guardian can switch charges during a battle, but doing so requires an action as the guardian re-focuses his attention.</p>\n<p>The character receives a benny each time he takes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}) while defending another character (Extra or Wild Card) during a specific encounter.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+, Notice d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"u3OrBCOPqYKWViTO"}
{"name":"Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This Edge is for skilled knife-fighters, who pride themselves on defeating their foes up close and personal.</p>\n<p>Close fighters move inside most weapons' reach, adding a bonus to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy weapon's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1 for that particular foe. No bonus is granted if the foe is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{unarmed} or using a knife or other small weapon.</p>\n<p class=\"embedded-example\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Lhazaar pirate with Close Fighting battles a Lyrandar heir with a cutlass ( @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} 0 ). The pirates @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} is raised by +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uKwUhLHnV0YQKSjX"}
{"name":"Skald","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Skalds are storytellers and poets and artists, able to recounter epic poems, plays, stories, legends, and other information from memory. Skalds learn special techniques for memorizing things he has heard or read, and is well versed in many topics.</p>\n<p>Pick any one of the following skills: <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge}</em>, <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore}</em>, <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}</em>, or <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Traditions]{Traditions}</em> and add +2 to the total whenever they're used.</p>\n<p>Additionally they may split their skill into two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Skill Specializations]{Skill Specializations} as appropiate.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Performance d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uWg212WyhZ87xLVS"}
{"name":"House Scion","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into the privilege of a dragonmarked house or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich} Edge), but she still walks in the elite circles of the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Dragonmarks]{dragonmarked houses}.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to take on the name of their house for a last name, denoting being a scion of the house.</p>\n<p>House scions add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with other house members. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the information about what is going on within their house, recognize family names or members of their house, or recall gossip concerning others within their house.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Dragonmarked Race"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uXtTievVirjiWxOC"}
{"name":"Storm Chaser","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When the weather is at its worst the character is at his best, seeming to read the storm like he would a book. Such characters are respected for their skill but feared for their love of a good storm.</p>\n<p>The character receives +1 to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} rolls made during a storm. In addition, the character may draw two cards during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases} each round during a storm and keep the best card, as long as he is the Captain. If the character has the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]{Wind Sense} Edge as well he draws three cards.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Boating or Piloting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_z6bv3ii8tjh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uiCxoLn8NjSVzJoK"}
{"name":"Adamantine Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged was created from a specially designed line made with adamantine giving him +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}&nbsp;instead of the normal +2 from Composite Plating.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"v1tb6IC0PLUjQRMA"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Druid)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Druidism d4+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_xoh0o6iqdor","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vB9AXT64SyZO4Cfp"}
{"name":"Fast Mount","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Mounting or dismounting a horse counts as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}. An adventurer with this edge can mount and dismount as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}, but may only perform one of each maneuver per round. Thus, the character could mount and dismount in one round, but he couldn't mount, dismount, and remount in the same round.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Rassilon Expansion II</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Riding d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vRZ83Ps3266CR4sN"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Undying Court","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vdB7lEZOIOElwR0L"}
{"name":"Finely  Tuned","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The artificer has studied under the best masters in his field and has fine tuned his creations to maximum efficiency.</p>\n<p>When creating an <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Device}</strong>, each raise an artificer gets on his activation roll reduces the cost of the power by 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}, to a minimum of 1. The Arcane Device must have the full points available to use the power in the first place before rolling. You only need to take this Edge once, not for each Arcane Device.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Slipstream Player's Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Artificer, Smarts d8+, Crafting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_m4fbu1ptbuc","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vfp3RwRgD9RIcYnn"}
{"name":"Favored Foe","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero has a grudge against a specific race or type of creature, and has devoted time to learning how to best such creatures in combat.</p>\n<p>When this Edge is taken, the hero must pick one type of creature, such as orcs, dragons, giants, elementals, fey, undead, or demons. He has +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} against his favored foe, having learned how best to engage them in combat. He also rolls a d8 instead of a d6 if he scores a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on an attack roll against them.</p>\n<p>This Edge may be taken more than once, but the hero must choose a new foe each time he takes this Edge.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Athletics, Fighting, or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wLlBuVVDDs94toJo"}
{"name":"Familiar","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage has acquired an animal familiar. The creature gained varies with the mage's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} when he first takes this Edge. Use the Available Familiars table to determine the type of animal a mage can choose.</p>\n<p>The mage and the familiar acquire the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.Loyal]{Loyal} Hindrance with regard to each other. The familiar is not a slave, however, and can refuse to follow orders, especially ones which will cause it harm. Unless ordered otherwise, the familiar follows its natural instincts. For example, a cat familiar may stop to chase a mouse, take a quick nap, or sate its curiosity about a small hole, and it's likely to hide during combat.</p>\n<p>The strong bond allows the familiar to resist the effects of beast friend. Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} of the mage adds +1 to the creature's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} for the purpose of how many Power Points are needed to control it.</p>\n<p>Both can understand each other's speech. To others, the familiar is simply making animal noises - the mage speaks his normal language.</p>\n<p>The familiar is a Wild Card with respect to wounds and the Wild Die, but has no bennies. The mage may spend his for the familiar, however.</p>\n<p>A mage can dismiss a familiar to gain another if he chooses.</p>\n<p>Each additional time this Edge is taken, the mage can pick one of the powers below. Each power may only be taken once. The mage may take this Edge only once each Rank. Taking it during character creation allows the character to take it again while he's a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The mage can transfer wounds and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} levels to or from his familiar as a free action.</li>\n<li>The mage may increase one attribute of his choice which is lower than that of the familiar by one die, to a maximum of d12.</li>\n<li>The mage can use the familiar's senses as if they were his own. This requires concentration. The maximum range for this ability is the mage's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 100 yards.</li>\n<li>The familiar can use the mage's Combat Edges as its own.</li>\n<li>Any spells the mage casts on himself also affect the familiar. If he casts armor with a raise, both he and his familiar gain +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}&nbsp;for the duration, for example.</li>\n<li>The familiar has 5 Power Points, which the mage may use as if they were his own. They recharge at the same rate as the mage's (usually 1 per hour).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic), Arcana d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wNFF04tNZUlP1ARY"}
{"name":"Disciple of the Sovereigns","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wltxN6Bw6kDl9ubO"}
{"name":"Takedown Move","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When the hero successfully @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Pushes} an opponent, the opponent must make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll at -2 (-4 if the hero got a raise) or be knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p>The wrestler can also chose not to push the opponent 1\" away, but just @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Wrestler"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wur3iMHKumf04wM0"}
{"name":"Improved Close Fighting","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Close fighters train to go for vital areas and weak spots for quick and lethal kills. The attacker adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll equal to his enemy's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Close Fighting"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xFjOqD0Yo62Sw3Io"}
{"name":"Boarder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Many captains instill courage in their men by offering additional rewards to the first man to board an enemy vessel. Few survive to claim their prize. Through skill and luck the character has survived dozens of boarding actions and feels empowered by the adrenaline rush.</p>\n<p>All @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls involving ropes are made at +2. Anytime he is the first allied character to board an enemy vessel he receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: 50 Fathoms</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Athletics d8+, Boating d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xPAq9wIpdfsw7br9"}
{"name":"Sunder","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves have an instinctual knowledge of materials. Those with this Edge know just where to strike objects or armored foes to cause the most damage. Any weapon in the hands of a dwarf with this Edge ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor} (in addition to any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{AP} value the weapon may already have) on a successful hit. The Edge applies against all forms of armor, natural or magical.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dwarf"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xl3BLynnzPEAUapL"}
{"name":"Born in Battle","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A good grasp of terrain and tactics, as well as knowledge of military history and enemy forces, can bring a general victory even when his troops are inferior to his enemy&rsquo;s. The character gets +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls. In addition, he gains a +2 bonus to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Battle d8+, Command"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_vbsguwz7lo","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Leadership Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"xr1Rg8tARYmKNi0C"}
{"name":"Necromancer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Necromancers are steeped in the lore and rituals of death. They are particularly adept at raising the dead and forcing them to serve their foul requests. While most heroes should avoid such vile sorcery, few can deny its efficiency.</p>\n<p>The benefits of the Necromancer Edge are two-fold. First, the Necromancer may cast the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} power at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice} level (rather than its normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran} Rank requirement).</p>\n<p>Second, when casting zombie , the Necromancer reduces the Power Point cost to 2/corpse. Additionally, he may double the cost per corpse to increase the Duration to 2d6 hours with a success, 2d6 days with a raise, or permanent with two raises.</p>\n<p>A Necromancer may never have more than twice his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} die in permanent undead servants.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Horror Companion</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Magic or Miracles), Spirit d8+, arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_8b17t4xj5w","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"y7k1NcYSkAE5jd29"}
{"name":"Disciple of Bolderi","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wc10m6m9sz","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Disciple Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yLz2cTqPw06ztk59"}
{"name":"Psiforged Body","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This warforged's body has trace amounts of psionically resonant deep crystal, providing her with increased psionic power and the ability to store psionic energy in its body. This functions as a mana stone (see Named Miscellaneous Magic in the Fantasy Companion) with 5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}. A warforged with this edge is sometimes referred to as a psiforged.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged, Arcane Background (Psionics)"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ylDTrIuYcOozM2NT"}
{"name":"True Berserker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Some warriors nurture the rage inside them, learning to call upon it almost at will. A True Berserker may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll to activate his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge at any time.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands, Dark Ages</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Berserk, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zHTBczFvYqQtIHeY"}
{"name":"War Cry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bugbear, Half-orc, and Orc can bellow an ear-splitting, nervewracking war cry that has been known to send lesser foes fleeing from the field.</p>\n<p>When used, the character may make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{test} against all targets in an area (as opposed to a single victim as usual). Place the edge of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} adjacent to the character. Every creature, friend and foe, within the circle must roll against the hero's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} total.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_lb6h1pgtb7c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Racial Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zPAIjnIDRYBukZ7w"}
{"name":"Ground Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The hero does not suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll reductions when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}. If engaged in melee against an opponent who is also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}, the hero adds +1 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (if @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}) or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} rolls.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility or Strength d6+"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ld1dvwzp8en","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zVgAMUPAzVo8ozsP"}
